{
  "texts": [
    "The bound in Corollary 2.5 becomes:",
    "It is also possible to transform the optimization on a discrete grid by an optimization on a continuous grid.",
    "Indeed, for any λ ∈ [1, n], we simply apply the bound to the integer part of λ, ⌊λ⌋, and remark that we can upper bound ⌊λ⌋ ≤ λ and 1/⌊λ⌋ ≤ 1/(λ -1).",
    "So the bound becomes:",
    "The arithmetic grid is not be the best choice, though: the log(n) term can be improved."
  ]
}